The '''City Attorney''' is an appointed position of the city of [[Bakersfield, California|Bakersfield]], [[California]]. It is one of five positions mandated by the City Charter and one of two positions appointed by the [[Bakersfield City Council|City Council]] (the other is the [[Bakersfield City Manager|City Manager]]). Similar to the City Manager, the [[Mayor of Bakersfield|Mayor]] may cast a vote on the appointing or removing of a candidate.<ref>''Bakersfield City Charter''. Article IV, Section 34, 37.</ref>
The City Attorney is responsible for representing the city in all legal matters. He also initiates legal action against an individual or organization, but only at the direction of the City Council. He also gives legal opinions to the Mayor, City Council, and city governments. The attorney also reviews and approves the writing of all city ordinances, bonds, and contracts. Her office is located in [[Bakersfield City Hall|City Hall North]].<ref>[http://www.bakersfieldcity.us/administration/cityattorney/index.htm The City's Attorney's Office]. City of Bakersfield. Accessed: 04-11-2011.</ref><ref>''Bakersfield City Charter''. Article X, Section 134.</ref>
